          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Inkwell opened in Brooklyn in 2014 as a place for tattooers who wanted to do their own work, at their own pace, without the pressure of a street shop. A decade later that is still what it is.</p><p>We take consultations by email and appointments by calendar. No walk-ins. No flash. No matching sister-tattoos on a Saturday night. Every piece on your skin is drawn for you, by the artist who'll put it there.</p><p>If that sounds slow, it's because it is.</p>",
